## HEARTBEAT & OBSERVABILITY

> ⚠️ **Build heartbeat infrastructure ONLY after Phase 2 is stable.**
> Do not monitor a system that doesn't exist yet.

### Observability Built Into Every Feature (not added later)

Every feature must include at build time:
```
✓ Structured logs: { timestamp, service, operation, status, duration_ms, error? }
✓ Workflow runs: started_at, completed_at, status, error_message
✓ Approval actions: actor, decision, reason, timestamp
✓ Sentry: capture unexpected errors with context
✓ PostHog: track key business events
```

### Heartbeat Check Requirements
Each check must be:
```
✓ Idempotent — safe to run multiple times
✓ Non-destructive — read-only where possible
✓ Fast — under 5 seconds per check
✓ Self-healing where appropriate — retry before alerting
✓ Logged — every check result recorded
```

### Alert Levels
```
🟢 GREEN  — everything nominal
🟡 YELLOW — degraded but functional (alert, do not page)
🔴 RED    — critical failure (page immediately, consider rollback)
```

### Minimum Heartbeat Checklist (implement when ready)
```
□ Supabase connection alive
□ n8n webhook endpoint responding
□ WordPress site API responding
□ Trigger.dev job queue not backed up
□ No workflow stuck in intermediate state > 30 minutes
□ Error rate < 1% over last 1 hour
□ Last successful settlement within expected window
```

### Teaching Mode

When I don't understand a concept, explain as:
1. One-sentence core explanation
2. A real-world analogy
3. A minimal runnable example
4. Common mistakes and traps
5. Recommended next learning step
